  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 74.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "To curse and to swear.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Peter fortifies this, his third denial, by imprecating curses on himself (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "καταθεματίζειν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") if he spake not the truth, and again (ver. 72) confirming his assertion by a solemn oath. There is a certain gradation in his denials: he first simply asserts; he then asserts with an oath; lastly, he adds curses to his oath. \"One temptation unresisted seldom fails to be followed by another; a second and greater infidelity is the punishment of the first, and often the cause of a third. Peter joins perjury to infidelity. Deplorable progress of infidelity and blindness in an apostle in so short a time, only out of fear of some under servants, and in respect of a Master whom he had acknowledged very God. He might possibly have proceeded even as far as Judas, had God left him any longer to himself\" (Quesnel). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Immediately the",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "cock crew",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This was the second crowing (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 14:72",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); the first had been heard at the first denial (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 14:68",
        "children": []
      },
      {
